<headline>Winter Weather Advisory issued December 14 at 4:49PM MST until December 15 at 5:00AM MST by NWS GreatFalls</headline>
<description>...WINTER WEATHER ADVISORY REMAINS IN EFFECT UNTIL 5 AM MST
WEDNESDAY...
* WHAT...Snow. Additional snow accumulations of 1 to 2 inches at
lower elevations, and up to 4 inches in the mountains.
* WHERE...Cascade, Fergus, Judith Basin, Meagher and Broadwater
Counties.
* WHEN...Until 5 AM MST Wednesday.
* IMPACTS...Roads, and especially bridges and overpasses, will
likely become slick and hazardous due to rapidly falling
temperatures with initially wet roads. Snow accumulating on these
icy roads will make the hazards difficult to see.</description>
<instruction>Slow down and use caution while traveling. The latest road
conditions can be obtained by calling 5 1 1 or visiting the MDT Road
Report website.</instruction>
